---
/**
 * Onboarding surface: a "first-week playbook" / ramp-up checklist on the left,
 * and a knowledge-capture panel on the right where the copilot turns what was
 * said in a meeting into a reusable, sourced answer. Editorial, grid-breaking
 * composition — not a uniform card row.
 */
---

<section id="playbook">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="kicker" data-reveal>First-week playbook</p>
    <h2 data-reveal>Turn week one into a guided ramp-up.</h2>
    <p class="lead" data-reveal>
      MacTranscribe builds a living playbook from your new hire's onboarding meetings — a checklist of
      what they've covered, and instant, sourced answers pulled from the tribal knowledge that usually
      never gets written down.
    </p>

    <div class="layout" data-reveal-group>
      <!-- Ramp-up checklist -->
      <div class="board" data-reveal>
        <div class="board-bar">
          <span class="tag">Ramp-up checklist</span>
          <span class="meta">Week 1 · Backend</span>
          <span class="progress" aria-hidden="true">7 / 10 done</span>
        </div>
        <div class="board-body">
          <div class="prompt">
            <h4>Your first-week playbook</h4>
            <p>
              Auto-built from each onboarding session. Every topic your team walked you through gets
              ticked off — and stays one click away.
            </p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li class="done"><span class="cb" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Dev environment &amp; access</li>
              <li class="done"><span class="cb" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Branching &amp; deploy flow</li>
              <li class="done"><span class="cb" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Who owns which service</li>
              <li class="done"><span class="cb" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> On-call &amp; incident process</li>
              <li class="now"><span class="cb" aria-hidden="true">▸</span> Data model walkthrough</li>
              <li><span class="cb cb-empty" aria-hidden="true"></span> Release sign-off &amp; QA</li>
              <li><span class="cb cb-empty" aria-hidden="true"></span> First ticket pairing</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="io">
              <div><span class="iolab">Captured from</span><code>Onboarding 1:1 · Tue</code></div>
              <div><span class="iolab">Time to productive</span><code>day 4, not week 6</code></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="aside" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="aside-lab">Saved answer</div>
            <div class="ans-card">
              <strong>How we ship to staging</strong>
              <span>Merge to <em>main</em> → Argo auto-deploys → QA signs off in #releases before prod.</span>
              <span class="src">source · Onboarding 1:1, Tue 10:14</span>
            </div>
            <div class="ans-card">
              <strong>Where the runbooks live</strong>
              <span>Wiki → "Onboarding" → service runbooks. Billing owned by Team Atlas.</span>
              <span class="gap">▏</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Knowledge-capture panel -->
      <div class="mock" data-reveal>
        <div class="mock-head">
          <span class="avatar" aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Onboarding copilot</strong>
            <span class="role">Capturing · Data model walkthrough</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="thread">
          <div class="msg them">…so reporting always reads from the replica, never the primary — that's the rule here.</div>
          <div class="msg you">Ask: "Why never the primary for reporting?"</div>
          <div class="msg them">Because heavy report queries used to lock writes. The replica keeps prod fast.</div>
          <div class="typing"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
        </div>
        <p class="mock-note">Captures the "why" behind the rule — so the next new hire just gets the answer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.55fr 1fr;
    gap: 18px;
    margin-top: 44px;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  /* ---- board ---- */
  .board,
  .mock {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e1417, #0a0d0f);
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    transition:
      border-color var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out-expo),
      transform var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out-expo);
  }
  .board:hover,
  .mock:hover {
    border-color: var(--line-strong);
    transform: translateY(-3px);
  }
  .board-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 11px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: #10171a;
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  .tag {
    color: var(--accent-ink);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .meta {
    color: var(--faint);
  }
  .progress {
    margin-left: auto;
    color: var(--good);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .board-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 1fr;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .prompt {
    padding: 18px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--surface-2);
  }
  .prompt h4 {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  .prompt p {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .checks {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--dim);
    display: grid;
    gap: 9px;
  }
  .checks li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .checks li.done {
    color: var(--faint);
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(45, 212, 191, 0.4);
  }
  .checks li.now {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .cb {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--teal-300);
    background: rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.14);
    border: 1px solid rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.28);
  }
  .checks li.now .cb {
    color: var(--rose);
    background: rgba(244, 63, 94, 0.14);
    border-color: rgba(244, 63, 94, 0.3);
  }
  .cb-empty {
    color: transparent;
    background: transparent;
    border-color: var(--line-strong);
  }
  .io {
    display: grid;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .io > div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .iolab {
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  /* ---- saved-answers aside ---- */
  .aside {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 18px;
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .aside-lab {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--faint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .ans-card {
    position: relative;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #121a1d, #0e1417);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 13px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .ans-card strong {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .ans-card span {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .ans-card .src {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }
  .ans-card .gap {
    color: var(--teal-300);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    animation: blink 1.05s steps(2, start) infinite;
  }
  @keyframes blink {
    50% {
      opacity: 0;
    }
  }

  /* ---- knowledge-capture panel ---- */
  .mock-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: #10171a;
  }
  .avatar {
    width: 38px;
    height: 38px;
    border-radius: 11px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--teal-300);
    background: radial-gradient(120% 120% at 30% 20%, rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.32), rgba(244, 63, 94, 0.14));
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .mock-head strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .role {
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }
  .thread {
    padding: 16px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .msg {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    max-width: 92%;
  }
  .msg.them {
    background: var(--surface-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    color: var(--dim);
    align-self: flex-start;
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;
  }
  .msg.you {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.22), rgba(244, 63, 94, 0.14));
    border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
    color: var(--ink);
    align-self: flex-end;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3px;
  }
  .typing {
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .typing span {
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--faint);
    animation: bounce 1.2s var(--ease-out-expo) infinite;
  }
  .typing span:nth-child(2) {
    animation-delay: 0.15s;
  }
  .typing span:nth-child(3) {
    animation-delay: 0.3s;
  }
  @keyframes bounce {
    0%,
    100% {
      transform: translateY(0);
      opacity: 0.5;
    }
    50% {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      opacity: 1;
    }
  }
  .mock-note {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--faint);
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .ans-card .gap,
    .typing span {
      animation: none;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    .layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .board-body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .prompt {
      border-right: 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
  }
</style>
